The paper deals with the problem of estimating a low-rank Toeplitz covariance matrix from compressed measurements, which is a problem in signal processing and information theory. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SP (Signal Processing) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes an improved approach based on random ultra-sparse rulers, which involves random permutations and hashing, suggesting that it may be relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper provides analytical bounds and experimental results, indicating that it may also be relevant to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
